    passage: `Philosophical debates often delve into the paradoxes inherent in human cog- nition. One such paradox concerns the relationship between free will and determinism. On the one hand, humans perceive themselves as agents capable of making indepen- dent choices. On the other, advances in neuroscience suggest that decisions are heavily influenced by prior experiences and neurological processes, potentially undermining the concept of true autonomy.
